history.text: Hello, I'd like to talk to you about Disney's Frozen
Sure. What did you think of it?
I thought it was the best animated musical to come out of Disney since The Little Mermaid and Beauty and the Beast
Did you like the music best?
Sure. You can practically see that the Broadway musical is destined to come!
That would definitely be interesting, but it seems like the great visuals would be lost.
Of course not! The script really delivers, it's a snowy pleasure
The plot was definitely well done. I found there were some interesteding twists, didn’t you?
Yes, I did! And could you believe that it was the 53rd Disney animated feature??
I know. They seem to get better each year. I think this one really reached out to both young and old audiences.
Do you generally watch movies with good ratings? What do you think of the 89% rating on Rotten Tomatoes?
I don’t pay too much attention to ratings, but I find most Disney movies to be instant hits with families. This one seemed to be a classic from the start.
The voice performance of Idina Menzel was spectacular! Don't you think?
Yes, she has a powerful voice and the song was a break out hit. I was definitely surprised with that character’s role in the film, though.
I did not like the scene with the the colony of trolls. I thought it didn't fit the plot well at all!
True. I also felt the snowman was a little weird, but he was cute.
Do you typically like movies of the comedy/animation genre?
I do, but I’m also a fan of musicals, which makes Disney movies a win-win.
Nice! Did you know that Jonathan Groff played Kristoff?
Yes. I thought he did a good job. I also really liked the reindeer.
A movie like this, really grips you emotionally, don't you think?
It does have a very different message than other Disney movies, It’s easy to empathize with the characters.
My favorite scene was when Anna and Kristoff reach Elsa's snow castle because it showed the pure beauty that could have been made from Elsa's magic!
Yes, that was some amazing animation. The action there toward the end was really exiting, too.
And of course Kristen Bell as Anna.... AMAZING!
I was not expecting here character to be so strong. I also didn’t expect their relationship to be the way it was.
I think that the animation was another strong suit of this picture.
Yes, it was a very pretty film. The scenery and colors really popped.

uid2response.feedback: I did not have a docuement. The other user was responding to me and the conversation was smooth, but there was not a lot of discussion on each element, and hardly any discussion of the plot. If I were more interested in ratings and who was in it that I was about the story, then I’d be more interested in seeing it after this conversation.
